Now look at a warrior.<br>
<br>
I currently have a 53 warrior ... that can barely kill a blue con alone, if at all. This is by far a solo'ing class especially with the gross under-con of most mobs in the game now.<br>
- I have no means of travel but to fork out money to get a port and constantly have to beg for a sow when my sow juice is gone. <br>
- I can not heal myself, only bind wound. You would not believe the bandaids you have to buy just to bind to half.<br>
- I can not buff myself long term, and the weapons and armor obtainable for those is higher end.<br>
- I may get dual wield .. but hey so do most melee classes .. not very class specific.<br>
- Sure I can taunt but get a ranger in there and the mob wants him... a caster is a better taunt (SH from a cleric with a red mob !lol)<br>
- My gear can be awesome ... in the high end game .. if I ever get enough money to buy them after forking out cash for ports and sow potions ... etc. NM the time I have to spend shouting for a port and running to find the wonderful druid porting or the wizzie TL'ing. I have seen more of the continents running to get to a druid ring than I care to ever see again.<br>
- I can take a hit, but without someone there to heal I am looking at 30 minutes down time at least to heal over 3000hp... horrible and stupid not to group.<br>
- My kick can damage 25 if I am lucky =) OOOO... uber damage<br>
I am sure you know where I am going with this. I created a cleric looking for a better life. I started my warrior because at the time my bf said it was the easiest class to start off on, and he was right. A warrior's life is short and is replaceable by most all other melee classes. Start one and see how much you really have to depend on other classes support to get you along in the game.<br>
Druids .... suck it up. You are the most spoiled class in the game !!<br>
